Wanted to share this casting call here from a project that I'm going to be working on, a MMA short film called Split Decision.

We had crew, cast, equipment, locations, everything ready to go, until our actress dropped out due to a scheduling conflict.

If you‚Äôre interested, or you know someone who could be interested please pass this call on, or email tomscottfilm04@gmail.com 

! VOLUNTARY ROLE: STUDENT PROJECT !

Food, drink & expenses paid for

This project is being developed at the University of Staffordshire, and will be filming in Stoke-on-Trent on the 15th & 16th November

items.text:
üé¨ CALL FOR CREW & PARTICIPANTS ‚Äì GRADUATION FILM IN BERLIN üé¨

Hey everyone!
I‚Äôm a film student shooting my graduation short film in Berlin (Dec 11‚Äì16).

üñ§ The film is an intimate story about love tested by trauma, about how the body carries memory, and how, even in moments of joy, the past can suddenly surface.
 It all takes place during a chill house party, where music, emotion, and memory slowly start to blend.
üß© Looking for crew:
* Production Manager / Coordinator

* Assistant Director (AD)

* Production Assistant (PA)

Preferably based in Berlin, with some set experience and a collaborative, creative spirit.
 This is a student film ‚Äì expenses are covered, and the atmosphere is warm, artistic, and professional.

üëâ If you‚Äôre interested or want more info, contact:
 üìß safeshore2025@gmail.com
üí´ Also looking for participants / extras:

The film includes scenes from a relaxed house party setting.
 I‚Äôm looking for open-minded people who feel comfortable being filmed and with their bodies.
 ‚ö†Ô∏è This is not a pornographic project ‚Äì it‚Äôs a sensitive, artistic exploration of intimacy, love, and memory.

üëâ To apply or learn more:
 üìÑ[ ](https://forms.gle/upDRMqiPHYRemdPU6)https://forms.gle/upDRMqiPHYRemdPU6

attachments.ocrText: May be an image of text that says 'ANMA ECLIPTICA 23 NOVEMBER‚Ä¢BERLIN BERLIN NOVEMBER I'm preparing here in Berlin part art, part inner journey. The idea is that every artist, dancer, or creator carries shadow inside, and that shadow actually hides their greatest light. During Anima Ecliptica, we use music, voice-and movement to transform that inner tension into pure expression- to let soul crea- te again. It's inspired by ancient wisdom schools, but it's made for our time real, artistic, human. This day will feature meditation and ritual work aligned with the astrological significance of the date.'

## **CASTING CALL ‚Äì ‚ÄúTale of Two‚Äù (Short Film)**

**Logline:**
*‚ÄúTale of Two‚Äù* is a portrait short film about women‚Äôs strength, focusing on our shared experiences rather than our differences. Through small, intimate scenes, we witness key moments in the lives of two women as they navigate hardship, love, and resilience in parallel journeys.

**Production Details:**
* **Location:** Downtown Vancouver
* **Shoot Dates:** 1-3 days ‚Äì end of January
* **Format:** MOS (no sync sound) ‚Äì performances will rely heavily on expressive, facial acting
* **Union Status:** Non-Union / Volunteer Passion Project
* **Compensation:** Volunteer basis with **great meals, greater company, and IMDb credit**.
Select roles (requiring multiple full days) will receive a **small honorarium**.

**To Submit:**
Please send your **headshot and CV/demo reel**, which **role** you‚Äôre applying for and a **self-tape** with the attached actions **taleoftwofilm@gmail.com**.
Include a **slate** with your **name, age, height,** and any **unavailable dates**.
**Submission Deadline:** *November 25th at midnight.*

Casting Call!

*Starchild* is a sci-fi drama that follows the story of two scientists, Vanessa and Tanner as they take separate paths to deal with their grief. Vanessa through faith, and Tanner through science. It's not until they discover the origins of life itself, that they reconcile to start a family of their own. 

The film is heartfelt, honest, and powerful.

Please send resume, headshot, and (if applicable) demo reel to starchildcasting@gmail.com

Hello everyone, my name is Isabelle . I am the director of ‚ÄòBroken Promises‚Äô. 

This short film is about a personal experience of mine within a queer relationship that focuses domestic abuse and domestic violence in the queer community. I have posted before but we are still looking for actors / crew

Details below:

Filming dates:

-January 18th-24th
-February 24th-27th

Currently still looking for:
- Parents (mum & dad) 40-59
- Receptionist any age / gender

Crew we are looking for:
- SFX makeup artist (potentially)
- Sound or assistant 

This is a student film, provided we reach our target for funding all cast and crew will be provided with food or travel but ideally both üôÇ 

We are filming in South East London, our shooting schedule is yet to be 100% confirmed.

If you are interested is any of the roles above please email me at: 

il2664u@gre.ac.uk

Subject line: Broken Promises Casting Call 
Please attach your showreel to your email.

Thank you for taking the time read this casting call.

items.text:
Do you ever feel resistant to the business side of acting? You‚Äôre definitely not alone. It‚Äôs the part that I struggle the most with, but like it or not, it‚Äôs part of the journey. And it very often matters more than talent. 

In this video, my friend Jodie Bentley dives into the time-and-creativity struggle ‚Äî that frustrating loop where you want to create but tell yourself there‚Äôs no time, which leads to inaction or perfectionism. She also shares how recognising that ‚Äúno time‚Äù excuse can help break the cycle and bring the joy back into creating.

üé• Watch the video here: [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=XzDLqLTATCk](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=XzDLqLTATCk)

items.text:
Hi friends! I have a question for the group (especially for agents and casting, but also anyone)! I started acting seriously 20 years ago, when I was a kid. I started in theatre, have impressive training/education, pivoted to film 10 years ago, then took an extensive break. Last year I recommitted and spent a fair amount of time reacquainting myself with the industry and where it is. Updated headshots, portfolio shots, resume, self tape equipment, renewed memberships to the three main casting resources, etc. This year I booked a couple of live performances and a whole bunch of commercial work, several featured background, a costar, a short film lead, a short film supporting, and im about to film my first vertical as a supporting role. Here‚Äôs my issue/question:

I know we are heading into a slow season and I wanted to use this time to focus on getting representation. BUT I‚Äôve only seen one project. I don‚Äôt have a reel and that‚Äôs kind of important. I have a decent resume, imdb credits, and have made a lot of connections this year. I‚Äôve put a ‚Äúreel‚Äù together of past self tape clips, but I really need some professional footage. I‚Äôm not sure what to do. Is it appropriate to email production for footage? If so, how long after filming should I wait before asking? If not, or if footage isn‚Äôt available yet, what is the most professional thing to do? Specifically focusing on what agents/agencies would prefer. 

Thanks for any help!

‚ú®** CASTING CALL (Denver, CO) **‚ú®
Hey everyone! I‚Äôm casting for my first web series, **A Fish Outta Water**, shooting in Denver in late January 2026. I‚Äôm looking for **three Black women (18‚Äì24)** for the lead and supporting roles.

**Characters:**

Riley - Black woman - She is a quiet girl, the type to blend right into the wall. Riley has a hard time understanding math (who doesn‚Äôt?) and finds it difficult to make friends at school. Her best friend and confidant is her pet goldfish, Shanice.

Shanice - Black woman - A former goldfish and current ghost-girl. Shanice spent her goldfish life as Riley‚Äôs only friend; she knows everything about her. More importantly, she knows how to help her in her new ghost-girl form.

Issa - Black woman - Riley‚Äôs classmate. Issa is strong-willed and hopes others notice this within her. Deep down, she longs to connect with her peers, just like Riley.

If you‚Äôre interested, please submit through the form below ‚Äî it only takes a minute:
üîó https://forms.gle/QVpJUmzZjAjQE5W18

Feel free to share this with friends who act! Let‚Äôs make something dope together üíôüé¨

items.text:
Still looking for volunteers for a Short film project who like to act in front of the camera.

The purpose of this short film is to create a new showreel for every actor and actress who‚Äôs gonna participate on it.

What's the movie supposed to be about?

A young man, once part of an underground operation supplying drugs to his boss, has since left the shady business to start a normal life.

Months later, he returns to the warehouse to surprise his former boss with a gift - but as he steps inside, he's struck by how much has changed. The familiar place now feels foreign, guarded, and tense.

After a brief, uneasy reunion, he runs into an old colleague, haunted by the past, does everything he can to avoid her before quickly leaving - closing the door on a life he's no longer part of.

Actors must be able to speak in English fluently!!

Open roles 

(Melly) Female, 18+

(Tasha) Female, 18+

(Maddie) Female, 18+

(Avi) Male, 45+

Extra 

Female & Male any ethnicity and 20+

For the spin

This will be shot in Cologne 

2 day between November 24-30 2025

If interested and available please send headshot to email officialemmanuelbenjamin@gmail.com

items.text:
PART 5 ‚Äî ‚ÄúTHE THINGS I COULDN‚ÄôT SAY‚Äù

The streetlights flickered like they were listening. She stood in front of him, fingers nervously brushing against her jacket, eyes searching his face for a sign ‚Äî any sign ‚Äî that it was okay to finally speak.

‚ÄúI don‚Äôt even know where to start,‚Äù she said softly, her voice barely cutting through the hum of the night. ‚ÄúYou‚Äôve been in my mind‚Ä¶ even when I tried to forget. Every corner of this city reminds me of you. Every sound, every light. It‚Äôs like the city itself kept whispering your name.‚Äù

He didn‚Äôt say a word. He didn‚Äôt have to. His silence was steady ‚Äî grounding ‚Äî the kind that gives space for truth.

She looked down, exhaling. ‚ÄúWhen we were apart, I realized something. I wasn‚Äôt just missing you ‚Äî I was missing who I was when you were around. You made me feel‚Ä¶ safe. Seen. Like the noise in my head finally quieted down.‚Äù

Her voice cracked slightly. ‚ÄúI‚Äôve gone through a lot, more than I ever told you. But somehow, with you‚Ä¶ I don‚Äôt have to hide. I can just be.‚Äù

She looked up again, eyes shimmering under the streetlight.
‚ÄúSo, this is me ‚Äî no walls, no pretending. I‚Äôve been waiting for this chance to tell you‚Ä¶ I still feel it. Every bit of it.‚Äù

The city seemed to hold its breath. He took a small step forward ‚Äî not rushing, not hesitating ‚Äî just closing the distance the silence had built.

And when his hand reached hers, it wasn‚Äôt fireworks or loud music.
It was calm.
It was peace.

Hi! We are LOOKING FOR MALE ACTORS for a short film here in Budapest, set during World War II, and we aim to shoot over 2 days in late February 2025 in the H≈±v√∂sv√∂lgy area.

The title for the film is KITART√ÅS. It is a short film set during the Siege of Budapest and is a psychological exploration of the raw emotional cost in war times. The story follows Hungarian soldiers as they face a moral and physical struggle for survival in the last year of the war in Hungary. All roles require fluency in both English (for crew communication/rehearsals) and Hungarian (as the film's dialogue will be in Hungarian).

We are looking for people to play the following roles.

MIKL√ìS:

Character Description: A young Hungarian field medic who carries no weapon. Mikl√≥s is haunted and fragile, facing a moral and physical struggle to survive as his faith in the war collapses around him.

Requirements:

Male, 20‚Äì25 years old.

Must speak fluent English and Hungarian.

Comfortable performing in outdoor winter conditions.

√ÅD√ÅM:

Character Description: A Hungarian soldier under Istv√°n‚Äôs command. √Åd√°m is a man torn between obedience to his orders and the stirrings of his own conscience and guilt. His internal conflict becomes a major turning point in the film.

Requirements:

Male, 25‚Äì30 years old.

Must speak fluent English and Hungarian.

Comfortable performing in outdoor winter conditions.

Strong dramatic ability and emotional range.

If you would like to be considered, please send your headshots, short introduction, and (if available) a showreel or acting CV to:

‚úâÔ∏è contactingdianag@gmail.com

EXTRAS NEEDED!

We need THEATER-GOERS and JURORS for a 4th-year UNCSA film called KRANKY FRANKY. Here are the details: 

THEATER-GOERS

75-100 audience members to populate a film premiere. Business casual attire. Any age is acceptable. Needed 11/22. LOCATION: WINSTON-SALEM, NC

JURORS

12 jurors who will witness the courtroom showdown! Semi-formal attire. Any age is acceptable. Needed 11/24. LOCATION: LEXINGTON, NC

KRANKY FRANKY is a satirical courtroom comedy with screaming matches, incompetent lawyers and animated sequences. Reach out to [krankyfrankyfilm@gmail.com](mailto:krankyfrankyfilm@gmail.com) for more details about time and place.

items.summary:
EXTRAS NEEDED!

We need THEATER-GOERS and JURORS for a 4th-year UNCSA film called KRANKY FRANKY. Here are the details: 

THEATER-GOERS

75-100 audience members to populate a film premiere. Business casual attire. Any age is acceptable. Needed 11/22. LOCATION: WINSTON-SALEM, NC

JURORS

12 jurors who will witness the courtroom showdown! Semi-formal attire. Any age is acceptable. Needed 11/24. LOCATION: LEXINGTON, NC

KRANKY FRANKY is a satirical courtroom comedy with screaming matches, incompetent lawyers and animated sequences. Reach out to [krankyfrankyfilm@gmail.com](mailto:krankyfrankyfilm@gmail.com) for more details about time and place.

items.text:
**Freelance Performers Wanted ‚Äì Join the Pink Pixie Parties Team!**

We‚Äôre growing fast and expanding into **London and surrounding areas**, alongside our regular regions in **Yorkshire, Nottinghamshire & Lincolnshire**.
If you‚Äôre **based south of Leeds**, or within easy reach of **Northampton, Wales, or London**, please do get in touch ‚Äî we‚Äôd love to hear from you!

We‚Äôre looking for bright, confident **performers** to join our incredible team! If you‚Äôre reliable, full of energy, and love working with children, you‚Äôll fit right in. Our roles include performing as **Princesses, Popstars and more** at birthday parties and corporate events.

**Pay:**
* 1 hour ‚Äì **¬£75 **plus travel door to door
* 2 hours ‚Äì **¬£95 **plus travel door to door
* Travelling more than 1.5 hours? Earn **from ¬£180 for 2 HOURS!**
*(plus mileage at 35p per mile door-to-door + ¬£40 travel time allowance)*

We believe in paying fairly for your time, professionalism, and performance ‚Äî our rates are **some of the best in the industry.**

**Why work with us:**
* Full **training provided** ‚Äì no experience needed, just enthusiasm!
* A **supportive, friendly team** that truly looks after each other
* **Fun, flexible weekend work** with consistent bookings
* A company that values creativity, fairness, and professionalism

**Costumes fit UK sizes 8‚Äì10/12**
**Must drive** and have **great **weekend availability (rolling 4-month basis)

We have **immediate starts available** and **bookings coming in daily**, so don‚Äôt delay ‚Äî send your details over today!

**Email only** (we won‚Äôt be checking Messenger):
b**ecky@pinkpixieparties.co.uk**

Please include:
* Your location and postcode
* Weekend availability from now until February
* Any relevant experience
* A recent photo or headshot
* Your **Instagram handle** so we can connect

Follow us:

If you‚Äôre **based south of Leeds**, or within easy reach of **Northampton, Wales, or London**, please do get in touch ‚Äî we‚Äôd love to hear from you!

**Pay:**

items.text:
PAID CASTING CALL

We are final year students at Solent University filming our Final Major Project, being mentored by award winning director Remi Itani. 

We are aiming to shoot between the 9th and the 24th of March 2026 for approximately 7 days. 

We are looking for 2 young adults to play our main characters Lily and James. 

Both roles will be paid and travel expenses will be reimbursed.

To apply please email our producer Anna at 0svina12@solent.ac.uk with your full name, headshots, and showreel. 

The deadline for application: December 1st 2025.

items.text:
Hey!

My name is Dom, I‚Äôm a director based in West London and am shooting a micro short on the 16th of November. It follows neo-realism style and is for a tiktok page called Ewanlyall_ with around 66k followers. It‚Äôs about a young man and mother who are evicted from their flat after an unfair rent increase. You‚Äôd only be needed for a short amount of time and sadly would be little pay (¬£20) as is 0 budget. We are looking for a woman aged around 40-60 and Shooting will be in Ealing, West London. You can also apply too if you don't fit this description as we are looking for other actors too!

A bit about me - I'm 24 and have produced festival nominated films as well as recently directing a commercial project for KFC and currently Accord healthcare. I am wanting to take the next step moving away from commercial projects to more meaningful projects and this will be my first of many!

PM me if interested!

Best,

Dom

We are looking for a Production Designer to join our WWII short film KITART√ÅS, a WWII short film set during the Siege of Budapest, 1944-45.

The role covers costume coordination, set dressing, and prop design.

Small-budget but paid production, with a passionate, bilingual team based in Budapest.

üìç Location: Budapest area (H≈±v√∂sv√∂lgy)

üé• Shoot dates: 2 days, late February 2026

üí∞ Paid position

Responsibilities:

* Design and coordinate WWII-era uniforms and costumes

* Create and source props and small set elements

* Ensure historical accuracy for 1944-45 Budapest

* Collaborate closely with the Director and DOP to build the film‚Äôs visual atmosphere

Requirements:

* Some experience in production design, set, or costume departments

* Creative, organized, and self-driven

* Speaks English (Hungarian is a plus)

* Interest in historical or period filmmaking is a plus

üì© To apply, please send a short introduction, your portfolio or photos of past work, and your availability.

‚úâÔ∏è contactingdianag@gmail.com

items.text:
Hello everyone,

My name is Kayuran Moodley, and I am the founder of KM PICTURES, a newly established mobile film production based in Chatsworth, Durban. I‚Äôm currently in the process of expanding my team and looking for dedicated individuals to join me on this creative journey.

At this stage, I am specifically looking for:
üé• Camera Operator ‚Äì someone passionate about cinematography, able to work creatively with mobile or professional cameras, and interested in learning and experimenting with visual storytelling.
‚úÇÔ∏è Video Editor ‚Äì someone skilled in editing, sound design, and color grading, with a good eye for pacing, emotion, and storytelling (experience in horror or suspense genres will be an advantage).

KM PICTURES was started with a simple but powerful goal ‚Äî to create meaningful stories from small beginnings, using whatever tools and talent we have available. I believe in teamwork, creativity, and growth. This is a zero-budget project for now, but it‚Äôs built on passion, vision, and the goal of developing something great together from the ground up.

I‚Äôm currently working on my latest film script, and I want to collaborate with individuals who are serious about learning, growing, and being part of a local production that has the potential to expand into something bigger.

If you‚Äôre a filmmaker, editor, or someone who simply loves the art of storytelling and wants to build a future in film, I would love to connect with you. Let‚Äôs grow this production together and create something unique in the South African film space.

üìç Preferred Location: Chatsworth / Durban (for easier travel and teamwork)
üíº Production: Mobile Film (Independent / Zero Budget)
üìû Contact: 061 046 3076

Let‚Äôs bring creativity to life ‚Äî together.
‚Äî Kayuran Moodley
Founder & Director
KM PICTURES üé•

#KMPictures #FilmProduction #DurbanFilmmakers #IndependentFilm #CameraOperator #VideoEditor #Teamwork #FilmCrew #HorrorFilm #MobileFilmmaking #SouthAfricanCinema #PassionProject #CreativityInActio

items.text:
We have an exciting opportunity coming up this Christmas and would love to get you involved in spreading the Christmas cheer!

 

Tesco are hosting an exciting Christmas Experience campaign, and we‚Äôre on the lookout for enthusiastic **Actors **to join our touring Christmas Roadshow. The event will take place in the car park and foyer of selected Tesco stores, featuring Christmas Chalets and a magical Christmas Grotto. Taking part in a child centered experience involving live characters and an interactive environment, we‚Äôre bringing the best performers and actors together to make this Christmas one to remember!

 

**‚ú® Assignment Details:**
* **Dates:** Between 24th November ‚Äì 12th December.
* **Hours:** 10am ‚Äì 8pm.
* **Locations Available:**
* Leyland             
* Preston             
* Blackpool        
* Southport        
* Litherland        
* Liverpool          
* Walsall              
* Bedworth         
* Bedford             
* Royston            
* Welwyn Garden City 
* Coventry          

 

**üéÅ What We‚Äôre Looking For**

As an Elf based in the Grotto, joining us on this journey to;
* Be passionate about Christmas.
* Create lasting memories.
* Have a charming, warm enthusiastic personality committed to delivering a magical experience.
* Provide presence/showmanship with exceptional customer service/communication skills.
* Reliable, punctual, and able to maintain a professional attitude whilst saying in character for the duration of the event.
* Your interactions with children will be heartwarming, patient and filled with the magic of the season.
* Please provide a showreel/video of previous acting/Elf experiences.

**Ready to join the Christmas magic?**

‚ú®**Register with us:** [https://ba.n2o.co.uk/](https://ba.n2o.co.uk/)

üëâ **Self-book now:** [https://myn2o.app/](https://myn2o.app/)
or
üìß **Email:** [alex.kourkoulos@n2o.co.uk](mailto:alex.kourkoulos@n2o.co.uk) for more details

Make this Christmas one to remember ‚Äì be part of Tesco‚Äôs festive celebration! üéÑ‚ú®

Personal Short Film Project

SEEKING 2 ACTORS FOR MAIN CAST

WHEN: Dec 20‚Äì23, 2025

PAID: CAD $150 / Day

Project Title:

The Thought Experiment ‚ÄúMETA MONTAGE‚Äù

Genre:

Meta-psychological Drama / Experimental Metafiction / Postmodern Romance

Logline:

When a screenwriter finds himself inside the very film he‚Äôs writing, reality and fiction intertwine ‚Äî forcing him, his characters, and even the audience to confront the question: Who is truly creating whom?

A visual and interactive interpretation of the Multiverse Theory.

Production Details:

Dates: December 20‚Äì23, 2025

Location: Vancouver, BC

Rate: CAD $150 / day

Type: Independent Short Film (non-union, paid)

Casting:

JACK (30s)

An expressive man in his 30s. Starts as a victim tied to a chair but gradually becomes both the actor and writer of the film. Moves between fiction and reality, showing layers of vulnerability and control.

Keywords: Actor / Writer / Victim / Meta-role

Look: Half-dressed, sweaty, bloody ‚Üí later calm and casual.

NARRATOR (30s‚Äì40s)

A calm, mysterious man in a classic suit. Both inside and outside the film, he speaks directly to the camera as a philosophical observer. His emotions slowly break through his composed tone.

Keywords: Narrator / Observer / Director-like

Look: Formal, mustache, black & white lighting, under spotlight.

I‚Äôll be sending those who emailed me a 6-minute short film I recently shot, along with a script excerpt from the project.

I‚Äôd really appreciate it if you could send me a video of yourself reading the script by November 23

Contact:

Director / Writer / Producer : Yuri Kakuya

üìß hkjfilm@gmail.com

Hi everyone! I'm casting a **voice over commercial **for StatsCan, and we are looking for people (men and women, 25-75 years old) that can speak **Inuktitut. **These ads will run across TV, Web and Radio.

If you're interested in auditioning, please email me at: **adriennelindsaycasting@gmail.com** for details. I will send you the script of an ad we did a few years ago. To audition, you will need to record yourself reading the ad and send it in to me. We are looking for "official-sounding" reads.

**Specs**:

South Baffin (Inuktitut Nunavut) dialect.
*Talent can be based anywhere, but will need access to a professional recording studio to patch in.*

Usage: voice over commercial - multiple spots across TV, Web and Radio. Open to both ACTRA & non-union performers.

Thank you!

Casting Call for Short 10-15 minutes called Repossession 

This is a  darkly comic short about ambition, fame, and the unexpected horrors lurking behind a routine job.

Casting call for the characters 
Kyle
 A seasoned presenter clinging to relevance in a changing media landscape. Desperate for a comeback, he takes one last job‚Äîblinded by ambition, even when the warning signs turn supernatural.
 Playing Age: Early 30s to mid 40s
 Ethnicity: Any
 Gender: Male
Spencer
 Kyle‚Äôs loyal second-in-command, tasked with shaping the show‚Äôs content. Often dragged into eerie locations, Spencer must confront whether he‚Äôs valued as a partner‚Äîor just a pawn.
 Playing Age: Mid 20s to Mid 30s
 Ethnicity: Any
 Gender: Male
Carla Curses
 A flashy social media psychic with a massive following and a hunger for viral fame. Her pursuit of a haunted object leads to possession‚Äîtransforming her into something savage and inhuman.
 Playing Age: 20s to 30s
 Ethnicity: Any
 Gender: Female
Frank
Carla‚Äôs trusted cameraman, now shattered by the night‚Äôs horrors. Haunted and fragile, his trauma slowly pulls him into the house‚Äôs darkness.
Playing Age: 30s to 40s
Ethnicity: Any
Physicality: Tall and lanky
Gender: Male

Filming will take place in the Liverpool/Merseyside area, United Kingdom. Looking to film middle to end of January 2026 
Please apply only if you're based locally.
For more details, contact: houndsoftheroundtable@gmail.com

Please note we do not reply to comments or direct Facebook messages. Thank you!

**25th Anniversary Edition: International Physical Theatre Laboratory**

**December 13‚Äì22, 2025 | Schloss Laubegg, Austria**

*A transformative nine-day intensive bringing together theatre artists, dancers, choreographers, circus performers, and movement practitioners from around the world.*

The International Physical Theatre Laboratory has been a cornerstone of European physical theatre training since 2000, bringing together artists from around the world for intensive periods of artistic exchange, training, and creation. Organized by NIPAI (New International Performing Arts Institute), IPTL embodies the organization's mission to foster international collaboration and support the development of contemporary performance practices that transcend cultural and disciplinary boundaries.

Due to the intimate nature of the program and the desire to create a balanced, dynamic group, participation is limited to 15 artists. Selection is based on professional experience, artistic motivation, and the potential contribution each applicant can make to the collective laboratory experience.

**To learn more about the program, faculty, schedule, and practical details, visit: **

https://www.nipai.org/programs/international-physical-theatre-lab .
items.previewDescription: For performers and actors, dance and movement practitioners, professional artists and educators, theatre directors and stage professionals, as well as performing arts academics and students. Participants can receive a certificate upon completion.
items.title: International Physical Theatre Lab (IPTL) | NIPAI

**25th Anniversary Edition: International Physical Theatre Laboratory**

**December 13‚Äì22, 2025 | Schloss Laubegg, Austria**

*A transformative nine-day intensive bringing together theatre artists, dancers, choreographers, circus performers, and movement practitioners from around the world.*

The International Physical Theatre Laboratory has been a cornerstone of European physical theatre training since 2000, bringing together artists from around the world for intensive periods of artistic exchange, training, and creation. Organized by NIPAI (New International Performing Arts Institute), IPTL embodies the organization's mission to foster international collaboration and support the development of contemporary performance practices that transcend cultural and disciplinary boundaries.

Due to the intimate nature of the program and the desire to create a balanced, dynamic group, participation is limited to 15 artists. Selection is based on professional experience, artistic motivation, and the potential contribution each applicant can make to the collective laboratory experience.

**To learn more about the program, faculty, schedule, and practical details, visit: **

https://www.nipai.org/programs/international-physical-theatre-lab .

items.text:
Hey everyone,
I‚Äôm Michael Uchenik, a film student, and this December (11‚Äì16.12) I‚Äôll be shooting my graduation film in Berlin, a story that explores the connection between trauma, love, and the body.

The entire film takes place during a laid-back house chill party, a warm, vibrant space where something deeper quietly unfolds.
It tells the story of David, an Israeli man full of life on the outside but haunted by a trauma he can‚Äôt escape, and Leo, his German boyfriend who tries to love him hard enough to bring him back to the present.

It‚Äôs a film about the duality of what we show versus what we hide.
About love as an anchor, and how memories follow us even when we move far away.

I‚Äôm looking for open-minded people who feel comfortable in front of the camera and with their bodies to join as participants in the party scenes.
This is not a pornographic film, but a sensitive and artistic project that looks at intimacy and vulnerability in an honest way.

If this sounds interesting to you, here‚Äôs a link with more info.

https://forms.gle/ZZJw8THu6qSW6UoKA 

And please feel free to share it with anyone who might be a good fit üí´

Thank you so much,
Michael

items.text:
Casting Call ‚Äì Lead Role ‚ÄúLil Messias‚Äù in Bachelor Film Groupies (The Norwegian Film School) - Paid! 

We are casting for Groupies, an ambitious and visually striking bachelor film by a talented team of students at The Norwegian Film School.

The film explores the groupie phenomenon through a music film about a rapper and a fangirl spending one surreal night backstage. Blending realism, stylization, and surreal imagery, Groupies delves into themes of power, status, gender roles, and what it truly means to be human in a superficial, image-driven world.

Role: Lil Messias (‚ÄúLil Mess‚Äù) ‚Äì Lead
Lil Messias is an internationally acclaimed rap artist.
On stage, he radiates confidence, sex appeal, and dominance ‚Äî the perfect image of modern masculinity.
Beneath the surface, however, he battles growing anxiety and emptiness in a life fueled by drugs, violence, and meaningless sex. He is trapped in his own image and longs to be truly seen. (Age 20-30)

This role involves:
 ‚Ä¢ An intimate scene with the character Ninni.
A professional intimacy coordinator will be attached to ensure a safe, respectful, and transparent process.
 ‚Ä¢ A rap performance, including recording a song and potentially some choreography.
 ‚Ä¢ The creative team will also be developing a full artist brand around the character ‚Äî an exciting opportunity to embody a complete on-screen persona.

Actors of all ethnicities and backgrounds are strongly encouraged to apply.

Production Details
 ‚Ä¢ Shooting period: Between January 20‚Äì30, 2025
 ‚Ä¢ Location: Norway
 ‚Ä¢ Compensation: According to Norwegian industry rates (Tariff)

Travel expenses will be covered. (Europe only)

If this sounds like something for you, please get in touch. Please note that only shortlisted candidates will be contacted.

Please send location, portrait and if you have: showreel and/or introduction tape.

Email: deteramalie@gmail.com

items.text:
Hey everyone! My name is Jackson Smith and I'm a fourth year at CU Boulder working on my BFA thesis film! I'm looking to fill two lead rolls if anyone is interested:

Title: Intersection

Genre: Drama

Logline: The film follows three people who unexpectedly effect each other while trying to make their way through a normal day. Introspective and character-focused. Very open to collaboration!

Roles: 

**Kat (Female, ~18-24)**: A young adult trying to find her footing. Kat often finds herself pushing forward in an attempt to forget what is behind her. She has a troubled relationship with her mother and has not been in contact with her for some time. It is now the day of her mother's birthday and Kat feels obligated to get her a cake.

**Heather (Female, 30s/40s)**: Kat's mother, independent and headstrong. Currently working as a freelance consultant, she really had to hustle to get to where she is now. However, her success came at the cost of her personal relationships. Heather wishes she and her daughter could reconnect, but she's not sure how to go about it. It is now Heather's birthday.

Production Type: Student

Contact Information: jasm4113@colorado.edu, (720)525-9544

Run Time: Short, ~12 minutes

Compensation: Unpaid (there will be food)

Union Status: Non-Union

Hey everyone! My name is Jackson Smith and I'm a fourth year at CU Boulder working on my BFA thesis film! I'm looking to fill two lead rolls if anyone is interested:

Title: Intersection

Genre: Drama

Logline: The film follows three people who unexpectedly effect each other while trying to make their way through a normal day. Introspective and character-focused. Very open to collaboration!

Roles: 

**Kat (Female, ~18-24)**: A young adult trying to find her footing. Kat often finds herself pushing forward in an attempt to forget what is behind her. She has a troubled relationship with her mother and has not been in contact with her for some time. It is now the day of her mother's birthday and Kat feels obligated to get her a cake.

**Heather (Female, 30s/40s)**: Kat's mother, independent and headstrong. Currently working as a freelance consultant, she really had to hustle to get to where she is now. However, her success came at the cost of her personal relationships. Heather wishes she and her daughter could reconnect, but she's not sure how to go about it. It is now Heather's birthday.

Production Type: Student

Contact Information: jasm4113@colorado.edu, (720)525-9544

Run Time: Short, ~12 minutes

Compensation: Unpaid (there will be food)

items.text:
Exciting News !
I'm thrilled to share my book EDDIE'S BACK -- A gripping story that I believe would make a FANTASTIC MOVIE.

I've already WRITTEN AND COPYRIGHTED THE SCREENPLAY, so it's ready to go! Now, I'm reaching out to production companies, literary agents, film agents, and directors who might be interested in bringing this story to life on the big screen.

EDDIE'S BACK - May 1963, Eddie a popular teenager is intentionally hit by a car, which leaves him in a coma. It's 2025, Eddie wakes up. He is shocked and disappointed at what he sees. Until the ghost of JFK visits him and inspires him to make a difference.

Now Eddie 77 years young, realizes why he was kept alive and what he has to do.

However, a senior Senator with an agenda of his own is watching Eddie's every move and is prepared to stop his mission at any cost.

DREAM CAST (Just Imagining!)
#HarrisonFord - #CandyClark - #PaulLeMat - #RichardDreyfuss - #CharlesSDutton - #MarkWahlberg - #MatthewMcConaughey - #MargotRobbie - #RobertDeniro - #BradleyCooper - #TaylorSwift - #MorganFreeman - #NicolasCage - #GregKinnear - #AnneHathaway - #WillFerrell - #PatrickSchwarzenegger - #joancollins -#kellyopsal -#islacervelli - #JackHyde -#LaurenSanchez -#jeffbezos -#elonmusk -#JordonHudson -#parishilton 
DIRECTOR - #RonHoward

NO OFFICIAL TIES - JUST PUTTING IT OUT THERE AND HOPING TO GET EDDIE'S BACK INTO THE RIGHT HANDS!

TAGGING TOP AGENCIES:
#ImagineEntertainment - #IndependentArtistGroup - #WilliamMorrisEndeavor - #VerveTalentandLiteraryManagement - #TheWayneAgency - #CAA
And indie powerhouses like: #A24 - #AnnapurnaPictures - #PlanBEntertainment - #BlumhouseProductions - #KillerFilms - #Neon - #FilmNation - #BleeckerStreet - #ElaraPictures - #BigBeach

NO OFFICIAL TIES - Just putting it out there and hoping to get EDDIE'S BACK into THE RIGHT HANDS!

PRODUCTION COMPANIES I ADMIRE:
#SONYPICTURES - #WARNERBROSDISCOVERY - #IMAGEENTERTAINMENT - #WALTDISNEYPICTURES

PRODUCERS - I'd love to work with:
#MarkCiardi - #MattDamon - #MarkWahlberg - #WillFerrell - #TomHanks

NO OFFICIAL TIES - Just putting it out there and hoping to get EDDIE'S BACK into THE RIGHT HANDS!

#Eddie'sBack #BooktoFilm #Screenplayready #Filmadaptation #Moviepitch #Filmmakers #producers #directors #Independentfilm #IndieCinema #literaryAgents

WHAT IF EDDIE (HARPER) AND JOHN (MILLER) WERE FRIENDS IN 1963?

Let's make movie magic happen!

PEOPLE WILL COME!

They haven‚Äôt stepped foot in a movie theater in 40 years.
Not since the golden days of double features and balcony seats.
But one day, without even knowing why‚Ä¶
THEY GET IN THEIR CAR AND GO

Not for the stadium seating.
Not for the surround sound.
**But for something deeper. Something they‚Äôve been missing.**

They walk into the lobby ‚Äî wide-eyed, hearts open, like children.
The smell of popcorn. The hum of the projector.
A moment suspended in time.

They don‚Äôt blink when the clerk says, ‚ÄúTwenty dollars.
Because this isn‚Äôt a transaction ‚Äî it‚Äôs a Homecoming.

They find their old seats‚Ä¶ the very ones from their childhood.
And the screen lights up with a story that speaks to the soul.

**Eddie‚Äôs Back** isn‚Äôt just a movie.
It‚Äôs a bridge across generations.
A story that blends nostalgia, humor, and hope ‚Äî with just enough magic to make you believe again.

They will laugh.
They will cry.
And most importantly‚Ä¶
**They will remember.**

Baby Boomers will come.
They will bring their children.
Their grandchildren.
And one day ‚Äî their great-grandchildren.

Because *Eddie‚Äôs Back* reminds them of what was good‚Ä¶
**And what can still be good again.**

The one constant through all the years has been family films ‚Äî
**Stories that bring us together.**

Oh yes ‚Äî people will come.
Not because they need to‚Ä¶ but because their hearts tell them to!
And when they do‚Ä¶
**They‚Äôll thank you for bringing it to life.**

NAWAITU.
Buat je kerja. Berdoa, Usaha & Tawakal. Org lupakan kita kah, biarkan kita kah, tak pedulikan kita kah, macam kita tak sama didalam kelompok mereka, tetap terus bersyukur dengan apa yang ada. Dia yang lebih memahami, BUKAN MEREKA. Lagi pun mcm usia kita ni, memangnya harus dan perlu mengingati KEPULANGAN. Moga kita akan terus dikurniakan kesihatan tubuh badan dan akan terus ingat mengingati.

items.text:
Wanted to share this casting call here from a project that I'm going to be working on, a MMA short film called Split Decision.

We had crew, cast, equipment, locations, everything ready to go, until our actress dropped out due to a scheduling conflict.

If you‚Äôre interested, or you know someone who could be interested please pass this call on, or email tomscottfilm04@gmail.com 

! VOLUNTARY ROLE: STUDENT PROJECT !

Expenses & food/drink paid for

This project is being developed at the University of Staffordshire, and will be filming in Stoke-on-Trent on the 15th & 16th November

Hello we are a 3rd year project at the University Of Gloucestershire and are casting for an experimental horror in Gloucestershire from the 24th of November to the 2nd of December, payment to be discussed after expressing interest. If interested please reach out to this email for any other information: [benjamin.pasmore340@gmail.com](mailto:benjamin.pasmore340@gmail.com) 

Roles:

Sonya - character age 12 - casting range 12 - 14 or someone older if they have a young face

Grandmother - character age 60 - casting range 45 - 70

Mother - character age 40 - casting requirements: Motherly voice - this role has no image just their voice

Let‚Äôs be real for a moment‚Ä¶ üì∏

Headshots can sometimes feel like an extortionate expense - as a fellow actor, I get it. That‚Äôs why I keep my pricing fair, accessible, and realistic, without ever cutting corners on quality.

I see plenty of novice photographers grab a basic camera & kit lens then start offering ‚Äútoo good to be true‚Äù sessions in these groups for ¬£30‚Äì¬£100 promising they‚Äôll get you seen ‚Ä¶ but here‚Äôs the truth: Headshot photography is a specialist skill. Low end, inexpensive ‚Äúquick fix‚Äù sessions might seem attractive at first but buy cheap, buy twice. 

Invest in a real headshot session with an award-winning photographer who brings experience, artistry, and skill to the table and get it right the first time. I‚Äôm a working actor too so I‚Äôm in your shoes and evolve with the times to provide the most updated, admired form of headshots.

Expect powerful, cinematic portraits that casting directors always notice. Clients regularly tell me their new headshots have led to more auditions, more callbacks and booked work - that‚Äôs exactly what I aim for.

I‚Äôve had my fair share of awkward shoots; rushed sessions with cash grab cameramen who treated me like cattle, just another face passing through‚Ä¶ I started doing this job to change that.
When you book with me, it‚Äôs never rushed. We‚Äôll have a coffee, chat about your goals, play some tunes, and get you relaxed before the camera even comes out. My direction is creative and unorthodox - I‚Äôll get you talking, laughing, and thinking, so we capture real moments that show who YOU are, not just what you look like.

The results speak for themselves - my clients have gone on to appear in major TV shows, films, high-end commercials, and even land roles on the West End. Your headshot is often your first impression - let‚Äôs make sure it‚Äôs unforgettable.

üëâ View my portfolio: https://www.fandmmedia.co.uk/ryan-s-gallery

üëâ Book a showreel scene, cinematic monologue recording, self tape sessions & more: https://www.fandmmedia.co.uk

üé≠ On Spotlight? Enjoy ¬£10 off any package!

Ryan üì∏

F&M Media üèÜ Award-winning headshots that get you seen.

items.text:
A new platform called Performeo is launching in the UK in January 2026, and it will be completely free for actors, individual casting directors and agents.

Created after speaking to over 700 industry professionals, Performeo aims to replace fee-heavy platforms and make the casting process smoother for everyone.

For actors: upload your profile, showreel and get discovered without paying subscription fees.
For casting teams and agents: manage talent, communicate directly and reduce admin so you can focus on the creative work.

The platform also has strong backing from industry investors, including Paul Forster (co-founder of Indeed), casting director Kharmel Cochrane and producer/agent Rory Aitken.

But is it a good idea to allow everyone to sign up? How will casting directors know who is serious about acting and who is not? Will casting be flooded with actors who have no credits and poor showreels? Will this create even more mess for casting directors to deal with? People who pay for Spotlight at least seem invested and committed. Could offering a free platform for all end up putting casting directors off?
items.previewDescription: Intelligent software for Casting Directors, Talent Agents & the FREE Actor platform you always wanted.

**UL√òNNET**

Vi er et hold fra Potemkin, Den Jyske Filmskole, der er i gang med vores afgangsprojekt

Vi s√∏ger en mand i spillealderen 18-23 til hovedrollen Milo

Kort om historien:
En ung mand med et spiralerende heroinmisbrug vender hjem til sin syge mor for f√∏rste gang i m√•nedsvis. Han kommer for at bede om penge - men ender som et stille opg√∏r mellem k√¶rlighed og skam. Vi √∏nsker ikke at lave en film som glorificerer stoffer, men om, hvordan det nedbryder de st√¶rkeste relationer mellem mennesker.

Om rollen:
Milo er 23 og fanget i sit eget forfald. Bag afh√¶ngigheden gemmer sig en s√∏n, der stadig elsker sin mor, men ikke l√¶ngere kan b√¶re at blive set af hende. Skylden, k√¶rligheden og skammen eksisterer side om side i ham.
Rollen kr√¶ver en skuespiller med evnen til at udtrykke mere gennem stilhed end gennem ord - en fysisk og f√∏lelsesm√¶ssig tilstedev√¶relse, hvor sm√• reaktioner og blikke fort√¶ller alt.

Praktisk:
Optagelserne finder sted i Aarhus den 24. og 25. november.
Der vil v√¶re fuld forplejning p√• settet, men vi vil ikke kunne betale k√∏n, transport eller overnatning.

Hvis du er interesseret i at blive taget i betragtning til rollen, bedes du indsende et kort selftape af dummy teksten, der er vedh√¶ftet i opslaget. Send det meget gerne til mailen nedenfor.

Vi h√•ber, at projektet v√¶kker din nysgerrighed - og at du har lyst til at tage del i fort√¶llingen om Milo og hans mor.

Med venlig hilsen

Team ‚ÄúI Limbo‚Äù
Bastian Kapela
Producer, Potemkin ‚Äì Den Jyske Potemkin Filmskole

bastiankapela@gmail.com

Casting Los Angeles - Fashion campaign/Skit

Character: Julian (male or female)

Age: Late 20s to early 40s

Ethnicity: White

Appearance: Refined, tall, effortlessly stylish ‚Äî always immaculately put together, but never loud. Think classic tailoring, muted tones, the kind of man who makes minimalism look regal.

Voice & Presence: Calm, articulate, with dry humor and a quiet authority that commands attention without raising his voice.

Personality:

Julian is the embodiment of composure in chaos. A seasoned creative who‚Äôs seen the industry‚Äôs highs and lows, he moves through the fashion world with both elegance and discernment. He believes beauty should mean something ‚Äî that clothing is more than fabric, it‚Äôs language. 

Unpaid - Meal, Copy, Credit

Nov 18th or 19th

4 hours Max of work

üö® CASTING CALL ‚Äì FEATURE FILM üö® (RDE FILMS)

RDE Films is now accepting auditions for our upcoming feature film. We‚Äôre seeking bold, authentic performers with strong presence and emotional range. Following directions is extremely important to our process.

‚∏ª

AVAILABLE ROLES

Detective 1 ‚Äì Male, 25‚Äì35
Seasoned detective, weathered and street-smart with a strong personality.
Types: Jon Bernthal, Shia LaBeouf, Denzel Washington, Lakeith Stanfield, Benjamin Bratt.
Barrio-raised energy. (Willing to smoke fake herbal cigarettes.)

Detective 2 ‚Äì Male, 25‚Äì35
Experienced cop with a black-and-white view of justice.
Types: Lakeith Stanfield, Michael B. Jordan, Don Cheadle.
Raised in a good neighborhood; confident and disciplined.

Assistant District Attorney ‚Äì Male, 25‚Äì45
Strong personality, ‚Äúboss energy,‚Äù sharp and commanding. The quintessential lawyer type.

Killer ‚Äì Male, 30‚Äì45
Soft-spoken, intelligent, creepy, and quietly imposing.
Think Ed Gein, Arthur Fleck, Longlegs.

Racist Pastor ‚Äì Male, 35‚Äì55
Charismatic, silver-tongued, sly, and playful ‚Äî hides malice behind a smile.

Killer‚Äôs Mother ‚Äì Female, 40‚Äì60
Quiet, submissive, battered southern housewife. Soft-spoken and broken.

Killer‚Äôs Father ‚Äì Male, 40‚Äì60
Abusive, mean, southern personality. Stoic, intimidating, and abrasive.

Captain of Precinct ‚Äì Male, 35‚Äì65
Respectable, strong leader type. Endearing and commanding presence.

Missing Child ‚Äì Female, 10‚Äì13 
Smart, articulate, emotionally mature. Must be able to cry and portray broken emotion.

Missing Child‚Äôs Mother ‚Äì Female, 25‚Äì35
Loving, playful, fiery. Must portray grief, depression, and distraught emotion.

Angry Mother (Smoker Mom) ‚Äì Female, 25‚Äì35
Mean, vindictive, narcissistic with a bad attitude. (Willing to smoke fake herbal cigarettes.) Think of the mother from the movie ‚ÄúPrecious.‚Äù

Gang Leader ‚Äì Male, 30‚Äì40 (Latinx Preference)
Calm but powerful demeanor. Ex-convict type with commanding presence.
Ability to perform a Chicano accent required.

Detective 1‚Äôs Brother ‚Äì Male, 15‚Äì25
Barrio-raised, fiery, gang mentality. Must be comfortable with prop weapons near their face.

Creepy Teacher ‚Äì Male, 25‚Äì35
Friendly on the surface but disturbingly affectionate toward his students. Unsettling presence required.

‚∏ª

üì© HOW TO SUBMIT
CLOSED FOR NOW

items.text:
Casting Call for Short 10-15 minutes called Repossession 

This is a  darkly comic short about ambition, fame, and the unexpected horrors lurking behind a routine job.

Casting call for the characters 
Kyle
 A seasoned presenter clinging to relevance in a changing media landscape. Desperate for a comeback, he takes one last job‚Äîblinded by ambition, even when the warning signs turn supernatural.
 Playing Age: Early 30s to mid 40s
 Ethnicity: Any
 Gender: Male
Spencer
 Kyle‚Äôs loyal second-in-command, tasked with shaping the show‚Äôs content. Often dragged into eerie locations, Spencer must confront whether he‚Äôs valued as a partner‚Äîor just a pawn.
 Playing Age: Mid 20s to Mid 30s
 Ethnicity: Any
 Gender: Male
Carla Curses
 A flashy social media psychic with a massive following and a hunger for viral fame. Her pursuit of a haunted object leads to possession‚Äîtransforming her into something savage and inhuman.
 Playing Age: 20s to 30s
 Ethnicity: Any
 Gender: Female
Frank
Carla‚Äôs trusted cameraman, now shattered by the night‚Äôs horrors. Haunted and fragile, his trauma slowly pulls him into the house‚Äôs darkness.
Playing Age: 30s to 40s
Ethnicity: Any
Physicality: Tall and lanky
Gender: Male

Filming will take place in the Liverpool/Merseyside area, United Kingdom. Looking to film middle to end of January 2026 
Please apply only if you're based locally.
For more details, contact: houndsoftheroundtable@gmail.com

Please note we do not reply to comments or direct Facebook messages. Thank you!

üé¨ CASTING CALL ‚Äì ‚ÄúEVIL GNOME‚Äù

In this campy slasher horror short, a young pair of dancers at an 80s tribute show sneak out (cheating on their partners) and are forced to face the consequences of their illicit actions. Trapped in a life or death game against a garden gnome possessed by an evil spirit , they must fight for their lives.

We‚Äôre casting for:
üßë‚Äçü¶± 1 Male Actor (19‚Äì25)
Role: Fabio a cocky, self-confident, dancer‚Ä¶ drug dealer and aspiring footballer but a coward underneath his roadman exterior. Must have a strong London/ MLE accent. Costume will be provided. Must be available all day Monday 17th November 

üìç Filming Location: Egham, Surrey
üé• Project: 6-minute short horror film 
üìÖ Shoot Date: Monday 17th November (11am‚Äì10pm)
üéûÔ∏è Self-tape or message Deadline: 11pm 15th November

If you‚Äôre passionate about fun, bold genre storytelling and love diving into energetic, expressive roles, we‚Äôd love to hear from you. This is an unpaid role for actors looking to gain experience or add to their portfolio.

üìß Please email arjanbains20@gmail.com for the audition pack, or send me a private message to learn more.

Please note this role is unpaid, but food and drink will be provided.
